{"data":{"wordpressPost":{"title":"Shopify Theme from Scratch Part 7: blog.liquid","content":"<html><head></head><body><p><img src=\"https://www.tetchi.ca/wp-content/uploads/2013/06/part7_banner.png\" alt=\"part7_banner\" width=\"800\" height=\"186\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-3309\"></p>\n<p>This week we&#x2019;re going to work on the blog.liquid template, where the articles that you write in the &#x201C;Blog posts&#x201D; page of the admin are listed.</p>\n<p>Let&#x2019;s dooo this!</p>\n<p><!--more--></p>\n<h2 class=\"step\">1. Make some dummy blog articles</h2>\n<p>Before we get started with the coding, you will have to make some blog articles. If you&#x2019;ve already got some blog articles written, you can go to step 2. Otherwise, go to the &#x201C;Blog posts&#x201D; page of your admin and click the green &#x201C;Add blog post&#x201D; link in the top right to make a new article.</p>\n<p>You don&#x2019;t really have to worry about the content of each article, what I did was just dropped some <a href=\"http://www.lipsum.com/\">lorem ipsum</a> on those badboys (if you&#x2019;re feeling moderately badass, you can use <a href=\"http://lorizzle.nl/\">gangsta ipsum</a>). I&#x2019;d say make about 4 to 5 dummy articles.</p>\n<p><a href=\"/static/bf8336f70e031d18623ddc2abdbca17c/98c72/blog-posts.jpg\"><span class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\" style=\"position: relative; display: block;  max-width: 650px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\">\n    <span class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\" style=\"padding-bottom: 41.082802547770704%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url(&apos;data:image/jpeg;base64,&apos;); background-size: cover; display: block;\"></span>\n    <img class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image alignnone size-full wp-image-3330\" style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;box-shadow:inset 0px 0px 0px 400px white;\" alt=\"blog posts\" title src=\"/static/bf8336f70e031d18623ddc2abdbca17c/a111b/blog-posts.jpg\" srcset=\"/static/bf8336f70e031d18623ddc2abdbca17c/aca85/blog-posts.jpg 163w,\n/static/bf8336f70e031d18623ddc2abdbca17c/0954f/blog-posts.jpg 325w,\n/static/bf8336f70e031d18623ddc2abdbca17c/a111b/blog-posts.jpg 650w,\n/static/bf8336f70e031d18623ddc2abdbca17c/ce471/blog-posts.jpg 975w,\n/static/bf8336f70e031d18623ddc2abdbca17c/98c72/blog-posts.jpg 1256w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 650px) 100vw, 650px\">\n  </span></a></p>\n<h2 class=\"step\">2. Add the for loop to output the articles</h2>\n<p>Open blog.liquid, and replace its contents with the code below:</p>\n<pre><code markup=\"span\">\n<h2>{{ blog.title }}</h2>\n\n{% for article in blog.articles %}\n<div class=\"blog-article {% if forloop.last %}no-border{% endif %}\">\n  <h3 class=\"blog-title\"><a href=\"{{ article.url }}\">{{ article.title }}</a> </h3>\n  <div class=\"blog-data\">\n    {{ article.published_at | date: &apos;%b %d, %Y&apos; }}\n    {% if blog.comments_enabled? %}\n    - <a href=\"{{ article.url }}#comments\">{{ article.comments_count }} {{ article.comments_count | pluralize: &apos;comment&apos;,&apos;comments&apos; }}</a>\n    {% endif %}\n  </div>\n  <div class=\"blog-content rte\">\n    {{ article.excerpt_or_content }}\n  </div> \n</div>\n{% endfor %}\n</code>\n</pre>\n<p>What we&#x2019;re doing here is doing a for loop through the blog.articles array, and for each article we&#x2019;re outputting its title, the date in which it was published, how many comments is has, and the excerpt/content of that article. To see a full list of what&#x2019;s accessible through the &#x2018;article&#x2019; object, see <a href=\"http://docs.shopify.com/themes/liquid-variables/article\">here</a>.</p>\n<p>The cool thing about the {{ article.excerpt_or_content }} tag is that it automatically checks if an article has an excerpt or not. If it does, it will output the excerpt; if it doesn&#x2019;t, it will output the contents of the article. For example, if you look at Figure 7.1, it will output the excerpt because I&#x2019;ve written something for it.</p>\n<p><a href=\"/static/523b6e3c36b2a289f082f5c798682fe8/20ed9/article-content-or-excerpt.png\"><span class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\" style=\"position: relative; display: block;  max-width: 650px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\">\n    <span class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\" style=\"padding-bottom: 69.14498141263941%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url(&apos;data:image/png;base64,&apos;); background-size: cover; display: block;\"></span>\n    <img class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image alignnone size-full wp-image-3331\" style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;box-shadow:inset 0px 0px 0px 400px white;\" alt=\"article content or excerpt\" title src=\"/static/523b6e3c36b2a289f082f5c798682fe8/dbb61/article-content-or-excerpt.png\" srcset=\"/static/523b6e3c36b2a289f082f5c798682fe8/19bd1/article-content-or-excerpt.png 163w,\n/static/523b6e3c36b2a289f082f5c798682fe8/d3bcb/article-content-or-excerpt.png 325w,\n/static/523b6e3c36b2a289f082f5c798682fe8/dbb61/article-content-or-excerpt.png 650w,\n/static/523b6e3c36b2a289f082f5c798682fe8/6b691/article-content-or-excerpt.png 975w,\n/static/523b6e3c36b2a289f082f5c798682fe8/20ed9/article-content-or-excerpt.png 1076w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 650px) 100vw, 650px\">\n  </span></a></p>\n<div class=\"sub\">Figure 7.1: Adding an excerpt to an article</div>\n<p>You should now see a list of the blog articles that you created in Step 1.</p>\n<p><a href=\"/static/26c647505f7fd0b1c323731d23c696e2/84120/blog.jpg\"><span class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\" style=\"position: relative; display: block;  max-width: 650px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\">\n    <span class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\" style=\"padding-bottom: 89.85943775100402%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url(&apos;data:image/jpeg;base64,&apos;); background-size: cover; display: block;\"></span>\n    <img class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image alignnone size-full wp-image-3388\" style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;box-shadow:inset 0px 0px 0px 400px white;\" alt=\"blog\" title src=\"/static/26c647505f7fd0b1c323731d23c696e2/a111b/blog.jpg\" srcset=\"/static/26c647505f7fd0b1c323731d23c696e2/aca85/blog.jpg 163w,\n/static/26c647505f7fd0b1c323731d23c696e2/0954f/blog.jpg 325w,\n/static/26c647505f7fd0b1c323731d23c696e2/a111b/blog.jpg 650w,\n/static/26c647505f7fd0b1c323731d23c696e2/ce471/blog.jpg 975w,\n/static/26c647505f7fd0b1c323731d23c696e2/84120/blog.jpg 996w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 650px) 100vw, 650px\">\n  </span></a></p>\n<div class=\"sub\">Figure 7.2: Blog articles being listed on blog.liquid</div>\n<h2 class=\"step\">3. Add the blog tags and link to the article</h2>\n<p>Next, we&#x2019;re going to add some code to output every article&#x2019;s tags as well a link to the full article. Insert the code in red below.</p>\n<pre><code markup=\"span\">\n  ...\n  <div class=\"blog-content rte\">\n    {{ article.excerpt_or_content }}\n  </div>\n\n  <span style=\"color:red;\"><div class=\"clearfix\">\n    {% if article.tags.size &gt; 0 %}      \n    <div class=\"blog-tags left\">\n      tags:\n      {% for tag in article.tags %} \n      <a href=\"{{ blog.url }}/tagged/{{ tag | handle }}\">{{ tag }}</a>{% unless forloop.last %}, {% endunless %}\n      {% endfor %}\n    </div>\n    {% endif %}\n    <div class=\"blog-read-more right\">\n      <a class=\"btn\" href=\"{{ article.url }}\">Read more &#x2192;</a>\n    </div>\n  </div></span>\n\n{% endfor %}\n</code>\n</pre>\n<p>The output of the code we just inserted can be seen in Figure 7.3 below. Again, we&#x2019;re using the .btn class that we made in <a href=\"https://www.tetchi.ca/shopify-theme-from-scratch-part-5/\">Part 5</a> to save some time &#x1F642;</p>\n<p><a href=\"/static/51073e6cca1dd0de3db156a2709e1f71/e2ef2/blog-tags-and-link.jpg\"><span class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\" style=\"position: relative; display: block;  max-width: 650px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\">\n    <span class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\" style=\"padding-bottom: 61.02204408817635%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url(&apos;data:image/jpeg;base64,&apos;); background-size: cover; display: block;\"></span>\n    <img class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image alignnone size-full wp-image-3393\" style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;box-shadow:inset 0px 0px 0px 400px white;\" alt=\"blog tags and link\" title src=\"/static/51073e6cca1dd0de3db156a2709e1f71/a111b/blog-tags-and-link.jpg\" srcset=\"/static/51073e6cca1dd0de3db156a2709e1f71/aca85/blog-tags-and-link.jpg 163w,\n/static/51073e6cca1dd0de3db156a2709e1f71/0954f/blog-tags-and-link.jpg 325w,\n/static/51073e6cca1dd0de3db156a2709e1f71/a111b/blog-tags-and-link.jpg 650w,\n/static/51073e6cca1dd0de3db156a2709e1f71/ce471/blog-tags-and-link.jpg 975w,\n/static/51073e6cca1dd0de3db156a2709e1f71/e2ef2/blog-tags-and-link.jpg 998w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 650px) 100vw, 650px\">\n  </span></a></p>\n<div class=\"sub\">Figure 7.3: Article tags and link to full article</div>\n<h3>What are article tags used for?</h3>\n<p>Article tags are used to filter out the articles listed on blog.liquid. For example, if you click on a tag called &#x201C;wicked&#x201D;, only the blog articles with the tag &#x201C;wicked&#x201D; applied to it will be listed.</p>\n<h2 class=\"step\">4. Add the current tag to the title</h2>\n<p>Scroll up to the very top of the blog.liquid template, and wrap the first line with the code in red below:</p>\n<pre><code markup=\"span\">\n<span style=\"color:red;\">{% if current_tags %}\n<h2>{{ blog.title | link_to: blog.url }} &#xBB; {{ current_tags.first }}</h2>\n{% else %}</span>\n<h2>{{ blog.title }}</h2>\n<span style=\"color:red;\">{% endif %}</span>\n</code>\n</pre>\n<p>This will make it so that when you click a tag that we added in Step 3, the title shows which tag is being used as a filter (Figure 7.4).</p>\n<p><a href=\"/static/1492cf1df838c2aecfa0057911793451/84120/blog-title-with-tag-.jpg\"><span class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\" style=\"position: relative; display: block;  max-width: 650px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\">\n    <span class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\" style=\"padding-bottom: 60.6425702811245%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url(&apos;data:image/jpeg;base64,&apos;); background-size: cover; display: block;\"></span>\n    <img class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image alignnone size-full wp-image-3394\" style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;box-shadow:inset 0px 0px 0px 400px white;\" alt=\"blog title with tag\" title src=\"/static/1492cf1df838c2aecfa0057911793451/a111b/blog-title-with-tag-.jpg\" srcset=\"/static/1492cf1df838c2aecfa0057911793451/aca85/blog-title-with-tag-.jpg 163w,\n/static/1492cf1df838c2aecfa0057911793451/0954f/blog-title-with-tag-.jpg 325w,\n/static/1492cf1df838c2aecfa0057911793451/a111b/blog-title-with-tag-.jpg 650w,\n/static/1492cf1df838c2aecfa0057911793451/ce471/blog-title-with-tag-.jpg 975w,\n/static/1492cf1df838c2aecfa0057911793451/84120/blog-title-with-tag-.jpg 996w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 650px) 100vw, 650px\">\n  </span></a></p>\n<div class=\"sub\">Figure 7.4: The blog title now includes the tag that is currently being used as a filter</div>\n<h2 class=\"step\">5. Paginate the blog articles</h2>\n<p>Let&#x2019;s now paginate the blog listings so that the user is not shown 50 articles all at once. I&#x2019;m going to go ahead and make it so that 5 articles are shown per page, but you can change this number to anything you&#x2019;d like (note: there is a limit of 50 articles that can be shown per page).</p>\n<p>At the very top of blog.liquid, add the code in red below:</p>\n<pre><code markup=\"span\">\n<span style=\"color:red;\">{% paginate blog.articles by 5 %}</span>\n\n{% if current_tags %}\n<h2>{{ blog.title | link_to: blog.url }} &#xBB; {{ current_tags.first }}</h2>\n{% else %}\n<h2>{{ blog.title }}</h2>\n{% endif %}\n...\n</code>\n</pre>\n<p>Then at the very bottom of blog.liquid, add the following code in red:</p>\n<pre><code markup=\"span\">\n...\n    <div class=\"blog-read-more right\">\n      <a class=\"btn\" href=\"{{ article.url }}\">Read more &#x2192;</a>\n    </div>\n  \n\n{% endfor %}\n\n<span style=\"color:red;\">{% if paginate.pages &gt; 1 %}\n<div class=\"pagination\">\n  {{ paginate | default_pagination }}\n</div>\n{% endif %}\n\n{% endpaginate %}</span>\n</code>\n</pre>\n<p>If you have more than 5 articles in your blog, you should now see pagination links at the bottom of the blog template (Figure 7.5).</p>\n<p><a href=\"/static/8f6b9b39b83a8ad141a04511d33a219f/e2ef2/blog-pagination.jpg\"><span class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\" style=\"position: relative; display: block;  max-width: 650px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\">\n    <span class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\" style=\"padding-bottom: 27.955911823647295%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url(&apos;data:image/jpeg;base64,&apos;); background-size: cover; display: block;\"></span>\n    <img class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image alignnone size-full wp-image-3397\" style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;box-shadow:inset 0px 0px 0px 400px white;\" alt=\"blog pagination\" title src=\"/static/8f6b9b39b83a8ad141a04511d33a219f/a111b/blog-pagination.jpg\" srcset=\"/static/8f6b9b39b83a8ad141a04511d33a219f/aca85/blog-pagination.jpg 163w,\n/static/8f6b9b39b83a8ad141a04511d33a219f/0954f/blog-pagination.jpg 325w,\n/static/8f6b9b39b83a8ad141a04511d33a219f/a111b/blog-pagination.jpg 650w,\n/static/8f6b9b39b83a8ad141a04511d33a219f/ce471/blog-pagination.jpg 975w,\n/static/8f6b9b39b83a8ad141a04511d33a219f/e2ef2/blog-pagination.jpg 998w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 650px) 100vw, 650px\">\n  </span></a></p>\n<div class=\"sub\">Figure 7.5: Blog pagination links</div>\n<h2 class=\"step\">6. Add in some CSS</h2>\n<p>Finally, let&#x2019;s pretty this template up with some CSS. Open style.css, and at the very bottom of the stylesheet, add the following bit of code:</p>\n<pre><code markup=\"span\">\n/**** blog.liquid ****/\n\n.blog-title{margin-bottom:0px; }\n.blog-article{border-bottom:1px solid #ccc; padding-bottom:30px; margin-bottom: 30px;}\n.blog-data{font-size:13px; font-weight: bold; margin-top:5px;}\n.blog-content{margin-bottom:30px;}\n.blog-tags{width:800px; font-weight:bold; font-size:14px;}\n.blog-read-more{width:122px;}\n.no-border{border:none !important;}\n</code>\n</pre>\n<p>Your blog template should now look like this:</p>\n<p><a href=\"/static/8dbd21e891b69688c3bc0f05a47d7232/014e1/blog-page-final.jpg\"><span class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\" style=\"position: relative; display: block;  max-width: 650px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\">\n    <span class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\" style=\"padding-bottom: 92.04431017119839%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url(&apos;data:image/jpeg;base64,&apos;); background-size: cover; display: block;\"></span>\n    <img class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image alignnone size-full wp-image-3398\" style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;box-shadow:inset 0px 0px 0px 400px white;\" alt=\"blog page final\" title src=\"/static/8dbd21e891b69688c3bc0f05a47d7232/a111b/blog-page-final.jpg\" srcset=\"/static/8dbd21e891b69688c3bc0f05a47d7232/aca85/blog-page-final.jpg 163w,\n/static/8dbd21e891b69688c3bc0f05a47d7232/0954f/blog-page-final.jpg 325w,\n/static/8dbd21e891b69688c3bc0f05a47d7232/a111b/blog-page-final.jpg 650w,\n/static/8dbd21e891b69688c3bc0f05a47d7232/ce471/blog-page-final.jpg 975w,\n/static/8dbd21e891b69688c3bc0f05a47d7232/014e1/blog-page-final.jpg 993w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 650px) 100vw, 650px\">\n  </span></a></p>\n<p>That&#x2019;s all for this week!</p>\n<p><a href=\"/shopify-theme-from-scratch/\">&#x2190; Back to table of contents</a></p>\n</body></html>"}},"pageContext":{"isCreatedByStatefulCreatePages":false,"slug":"shopify-theme-from-scratch-part-7"}}